cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.FL

The paper discusses the interactive interpretation of sequential programs, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). It also mentions the connection between sequential algorithms and linear logic (cs.LO) and games (cs.LG). The paper also touches upon the semantics of programs (cs.SE) and includes explicit errors in the syntax and semantics of the language PCF (cs.FL). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL, followed by cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.LG, and cs.FL.
